  "status": "Review",
  "summary": "The default transaction behavior of ETH is *transfer-and-call*, but the widely used [ERC-20](./eip-20.md) standard isn't compatible with this pattern. This incompatibility forces applications to use an inefficient and risky two-step *approve-then-call* process. This approach is costly, creates a poor user experience, and introduces significant security vulnerabilities, as users must approve unaudited and often upgradable contracts. This has led to numerous allowance-related bugs and exploits. The **Universal Token Router** (**UTR**) addresses this issue by separating the token allowance from the application logic. This allows any token to be spent in a single contract call, similar to how ETH is handled, without needing to approve individual application contracts. When tokens are approved",
  "title": "Universal Token Router"
}